China’s Supreme People’s Court (SPC) on Tuesday unveiled 25 typical cases in 25 years concerning state compensation to celebrate the 25th anniversary of the implementation of China’s state compensation law. The court said that the release of the typical cases aimed at demonstrating the importance of the state compensation system in disciplining the public authorities concerning just judicature and law-based administration. Over the past 25 years, state compensation trials have developed healthily from the scratch, effectively protecting human rights and supervising public authorities, said Tao Kaiyuan, the Vice-President of the SPC. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The courts will firmly uphold people-centered philosophy and comprehensively improve the quality and effectiveness of state compensation trial, Tao added. (Xinhua/NAN) SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION